story.title: Too Late - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: Shannon: I’m so nervous about tonight.
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: I’m so nervous about tonight.
I don’t want to go to jail for robbery!
Omg you’re not going to jail.
We WON’T get caught.
How can you be so sure?
Annie’s got it all planned out.
We get to the party…
Steal her step-monster’s jewelry from the safe.
Leave with no one suspecting a thing.
Easy.
I guess…
Besides, we have to go through with it.
If we don’t, Annie will tell everyone our secrets at school tomorrow.
I can’t believe we’re letting her blackmail us into doing this.
Look, I can’t have anyone finding out I cheated on the finals.
I could lose my place at Yale. I have to do what she says.
I don’t know what dirt she has on you…
But trust me, she’ll use it if you back out now.
What if we went to the police? We could tell them what she’s planning.
We could tell them she forced us!
I’m already on the way to Annie’s house. The charity ball’s about to start.
If you don’t come, Annie will make you pay.
She’ll make me pay too.
Please, Shannon.
I know, I know, you’re right!
I just don’t need a criminal record.
And I don’t need anyone finding out I’m a cheat.
Okay, I’ll meet you at the ball like we planned.
See you soon.
Carys closes out her thread with Shannon—
And texts Annie.
Shannon’s scared. I’m worried she’s gonna back out.
What?? She has to come tonight.
We need to pin the whole robbery on her!
What’d you tell her?
That we have to go through with it.
Or else you’d spill our secrets.
What did you use to blackmail her into this anyway?
You really want to know?
Yes! Tell!!
She’s got a secret girlfriend. She doesn’t want anyone at school to know.
So if she doesn’t turn up at the charity ball you’ll out her??
I won’t have to. She’ll be there, right?
You both will. RIGHT??
Yeah, yeah, I’ll handle Shannon.
And I just got to your house.
I’m in the reception room. I can see you talking with your parents.
Rose is NOT my mother. She’s the step-monster, remember?
Right, sorry!
I’ll check in with Shannon now and make sure she’s coming.
Carys pulls up her thread with Shannon.
Shannon, I’m at Annie’s house. Where are you?
I’m in a cab. Almost there.
That’s a relief. We have to stick together, right?
You’re so right.
Look, I’m terrified too. But we need to stay calm.
Stick to the plan.
We’ll steal the jewelry from Annie’s stupid-rich step-mom, and then it’ll all be over.
Shannon’s cab pulls up outside a huge mansion.
The property seems to go on for miles.
Shannon walks through the front door and is greeted with a hum of chattering and glasses clinking.
Wow, there are a lot of people here! I don’t see you.
Just stay in the main reception room. I’ll find you.
Carys quickly texts Annie.
Annie, she’s here.
Good. This has to go down fast.
Make sure you slip out when all the guests are in the reception room.
While the step-monster is making her speech.
I’ll be right there next to her, so when the alarm goes off and she discovers the safe is empty…
No one will suspect I had anything to do with it.
I know the plan, Annie.
Don’t talk to me like that. I’m giving you twenty percent of what we take, remember?
So you have the combination to the safe written down?
Yes.
And you’ll slip it into Shannon’s purse when you’re done?
Yes.
That way the step-monster’s staff will find it on her. You’ll be clear too.
I know what to do, Annie. Just let me get on with it.
Fine. All the guests are here. It won’t be long until the speech.
I’m on it. I’ll find Shannon now.
Carys waves to Shannon across the crowded entrance hall.
Shannon waves back, looking nervous.
Annie’s step-mother dings the side of her champagne glass and thanks the guests for coming.
Slyly, Annie texts Carys.
Go now, Carys!
Carys tugs on Shannon’s elbow…
And together they slip through the crowd to the hidden side stairs used by the staff.
Carys gets another text from Annie.
Rose the step-monster is just getting started with her speech 🤮
We’re almost at the bedroom.
Remember, the safe’s on the left side of the walk-in closet.
Next to Rose’s collection of Louboutins 👠
We’re there. I’m making Shannon punch in the combination.
Her fingerprints will be all over the safe!
And??
CARYS??
It opened! The necklace is here!!
Get the earrings too. I want it all.
Okay, I have everything.
Good. Now plant that note with the combination written on it on Shannon.
Have you done it??
CARYS?! Rose is finishing up here.
We need everything in place to accuse Shannon!
It’s done!
You still want to me to stash the jewelry in the bathroom without Shannon seeing?
Yes. Pretend you have to pee and then hide it.
Rose would never think to look for it in her own house.
When I trigger the silent alarm, the cops will be here in fifteen minutes flat.
Rose will be too distracted by the chaos.
I’ll grab it all then.
Are you sure this will work?
What if Shannon accuses us?
Who’s going to believe anything Shannon says?
And like you said, her fingerprints are on the safe—
And the combination is in her purse.
A few minutes pass.
Okay, the jewelry is hidden in the bathroom.
Rose finished her speech a few minutes ago. She disappeared somewhere.
Tell Shannon it’s best if you split up.
Then get back down here with me.
I’m going to hit the alarm in one minute.
Wait for me! I’m coming!
Carys practically pushes Shannon down a hallway, which leads to a separate set of stairs.
She tells her to split up and that she’ll meet her and Annie back in the reception room.
Carys hurries, making her own way back to Annie—
Just as sirens wail in the distance.
Breathless, Carys reaches Annie.
The cops already? That was fast.
I guess Rose the step-monster is so important the cops are on speed-dial.
Where’s Shannon? We need to point the finger at her as soon as they bust in.
I don’t see her. Text her now.
Carys reaches for her phone.
Shannon? Where are you??
Open the front door.
What? Why??
Just do it or you’ll be too late.
Carys shows Annie the text from Shannon.
Annie and Carys look at each other…
Then run through the reception room and swing open the front door.
Shannon is standing in the sweeping driveway, just about to get into a sleek car…
Being driven by a beautiful girl.
Shannon holds out something that glitters in the moonlight…
Before she smiles, and shuts the car door.
The necklace!
Annie calls Shannon.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING??!
Ask Rose.
WHAT???
Shannon hangs up.
Annie’s cell phone immediately starts ringing. It’s her step-mother.
She hesitates for a second before she picks it up.
Rose? Where are you? Someone just stole your necklace!
Oh, sweetheart, I know.
What?? What’s going on??
A lovely young girl named Shannon came to see me a few days ago.
She told me everything.
Annie stares at the screen.
You can’t believe Shannon. She’s a thief!
I just saw her drive away with your necklace!
Who do you think gave it to her?
I had a new camera system installed, Annie.
I saw your friend Carys go into my closet…
And open my safe.
But…why would you give Shannon your necklace?!
Because now it’s not in the house.
It’s been stolen, remember, Annie?
At least that’s what the police will think when I tell them it was you and your little friend.
Meanwhile, Carys is frozen in place. She’s furious and unsure what to do.
The sirens get louder and Carys frantically calls Shannon.
Come back, Shannon! Please.
I gave you the chance to back out of this, but you didn’t.
It’s too late, Carys. Whatever happens now, it’s on you.
If I were you, I’d tell the truth. Annie doesn’t deserve your loyalty.
But what about the necklace?!
That’s a little gift from Rose to me.
Now she can tell the police Annie emptied the safe and stole everything.
You see, Rose has a copy of the texts between you and Annie planning this whole thing.
My girlfriend is a crazy good hacker 😉
Rose WANTED the robbery to go ahead. Now she can show the police those texts.
Lucky for me, I look good in diamonds.
Police cars pull onto the driveway, lighting up the house in flashing red and blue.
You can’t do this to me!
You did this to yourself.
Oh, and tell Annie she’s free to tell everyone at school that I have a girlfriend 😘
